[SPEAKER NOTE: The Educational Fund is perhaps the most transformational element of this model. For the first time in African education, the system generates the revenue to sustain and improve itself. The Fund finances everything that \u8220\'93free education\u8221\'94 currently leaves out: infrastructure, materials, teacher supplements, scholarships, and technology upgrades. Critically, the Fund is independently administered \u8212\'97 not by government alone and not by UMOJA-ai alone, but by an independent entity with a board representing all stakeholders. Annual external audits will be published. This ensures transparency and accountability in every dollar spent. This is how we break the cycle of dependency on donor funding and government budget constraints.]}
